SECTION 2: IMPORTANCE OF TIME (CRITICAL FORENSIC CONCEPT)

Logs are only useful if events are correctly ordered in time.

Problem:
	•	If system clocks differ → timeline becomes unreliable
	•	Attack chain reconstruction fails

Solution:
	•	Use Network Time Protocol (NTP)

Command:
ntpdate pool.ntp.org

Explanation:
	•	Synchronizes system clock with global time servers
	•	Ensures logs from multiple systems align

Example:
root@server# ntpdate pool.ntp.org
adjust time server 85.x.x.x offset 0.000060 sec

Check:
date

Forensics Insight:
Even a few seconds mismatch can:
	•	Break correlation between logs
	•	Mislead analysts during incident response

