SECTION 4: LOG FORMATS (WHY THEY MATTER)

Logs come in different formats depending on system design.

A. Semi-Structured (Flexible but predictable)

Example (Syslog):
May 31 12:34:56 server CRON[123]: job executed
	•	Contains structured parts + free text
	•	Requires parsing

⸻

B. Structured (Best for automation)

Example JSON:
{“user”:“admin”,“status”:200}

Advantages:
	•	Easy parsing
	•	Compatible with SIEM
	•	Machine-readable

⸻

C. Unstructured (Hardest to analyze)

Example:
User admin logged in successfully
	•	Human-readable
	•	Difficult for automation

⸻

Forensics Insight:
Structured logs are preferred because:
	•	Easier correlation
	•	Faster detection
	•	Better automation

