SECTION 7: RSYSLOG (CORE LINUX LOGGING TOOL)

rsyslog collects and routes logs.

Check status:
sudo systemctl status rsyslog

⸻

Create config:
sudo nano /etc/rsyslog.d/98-websrv-02-sshd.conf

Content:

$FileCreateMode 0644
:programname, isequal, “sshd” /var/log/websrv-02/rsyslog_sshd.log

Explanation:
	•	$FileCreateMode → file permissions
	•	programname filter → selects ssh logs
	•	output path → where logs are stored

⸻

Restart:
sudo systemctl restart rsyslog

⸻

Verification:
ssh localhost
cat /var/log/websrv-02/rsyslog_sshd.log

⸻

